items.profile_description:
COVID update: I have no symptoms and have tested negative in the past, but I still continue to wear a mask and socially distance. At your home I will wear a mask, and if requested I will put on gloves as well. Safety first!

I grew up around my grandfather who was a "jack of all trades" and we did a lot of work on things around our house and those of my family. I am currently a fully self-employed handyman--this is what I do full time, 8 to 12 hrs, every day. I can guarantee you I will know what needs to be done with your tasks. 

Before my current job, I was in the U.S. Navy and also worked in the maritime industry (cargo ships) so I am good at improvising, being resourceful, dependable, and honest. 

I've worked in New Orleans for awhile, where there are a lot of older homes, so I know how to recognize rare or unique craftsmanship and antique fixtures, and how to be delicate. My main skills include carpentry, painting, concrete, sheetrock, stucco, among various others for which a need may arise as part of living in a home. For example, in one day I built IKEA furniture, patched drywall holes, diagnosed a faulty garbage  disposal, painted a wall, and framed up a floor in a shed. 

I promise that I can help you with whatever you may need done, and if I can't, I will be upfront, let you know, and explain why.
items.rabbit_category_description: I have moved myself about 10 times, to 5 different states, in the last 10 years, so I think you could say I know how to get things moved effectively.
